1
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:41,573
[Episode 3]

2
00:01:47,959 --> 00:01:49,280
Hey, Hao.

3
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,120
Is there a girl named Qing Ye

4
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,679
staying at your place?

5
00:01:53,799 --> 00:01:55,164
She's checked into

6
00:01:55,164 --> 00:01:56,400
the ocean view suite.

7
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,382
Keep an eye on her for me.

8
00:01:58,382 --> 00:02:00,904
Let me know if anything comes up.

9
00:02:00,904 --> 00:02:02,000
Got it.

10
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,681
Thanks.

11
00:02:13,618 --> 00:02:15,175
Oh, no!

12
00:02:16,786 --> 00:02:18,240
Hey.

13
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,440
That room of yours

14
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,759
has been vacant for a long time.

15
00:02:20,759 --> 00:02:22,442
It's normal for things to malfunction.

16
00:02:22,442 --> 00:02:23,680
Look,

17
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,105
I need to download study materials.

18
00:02:25,105 --> 00:02:26,920
I can do nothing without the internet.

19
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:29,400
Then use your cellphone data!

20
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:32,280
I have huge files to download.
Mobile data isn't nearly enough.

21
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:35,400
Come on, lady, it's already so late,
and it's pouring rain.

22
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:38,246
The Wi-Fi repairman
definitely won't come until tomorrow.

23
00:02:39,528 --> 00:02:40,599
What about tonight?

24
00:02:40,599 --> 00:02:42,640
I'll give you the Wi-Fi password
for the room next door.

25
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,655
You can piggyback off theirs for now.

26
00:02:46,140 --> 00:02:47,480
What about the air conditioner?

27
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:50,657
The AC repairman
isn't coming until tomorrow either, right?

28
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:53,880
Fine.

29
00:03:10,594 --> 00:03:12,433
What's up, everyone!

30
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:15,440
Welcome to
the most amazing livestream you'll ever see!

31
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:17,960
Today, I'm about to drop some talent on you:

32
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,280
unbelievable, never-before-seen stuff!

33
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,920
I promise I'll blow your minds!

34
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:23,960
For those of you who just joined,

35
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:27,519
quick, quick! Hit that follow button!

36
00:03:27,519 --> 00:03:29,639
Welcome, "No Cilantro."

37
00:03:29,639 --> 00:03:32,704
Welcome, "Grass is Me."

38
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:36,680
I'll sing a song for you,

39
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,080
then hit a dance!

40
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:41,120
Send those little red hearts,
let me see them! Send some likes!

41
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,047
Wu.

42
00:03:52,047 --> 00:03:53,320
The camera is fine.

43
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:55,480
It's a network issue.

44
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,799
You're here early.

45
00:03:56,799 --> 00:03:58,936
It's barely dawn.

46
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,919
That woman in the sea view room.

47
00:04:01,919 --> 00:04:03,845
Who is she to you?

48
00:04:03,845 --> 00:04:06,109
Last night,
you rushed over in such a panic to find her.

49
00:04:06,109 --> 00:04:07,319
The client.

50
00:04:07,319 --> 00:04:09,600
You don't come across a client

51
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,599
this difficult every day.

52
00:04:11,599 --> 00:04:14,399
I heard you're short on cash again lately.

53
00:04:14,399 --> 00:04:17,239
When have you ever seen me not short on cash?

54
00:04:17,239 --> 00:04:18,399
What's up?

55
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,640
Got a job to refer?

56
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:21,072
Yeah.

57
00:04:21,072 --> 00:04:22,799
- Want it?
- If it pays, I'll take it.

58
00:04:22,799 --> 00:04:24,479
The more the merrier.

59
00:04:24,479 --> 00:04:26,929
So, do you want a gig to make some quick cash?

60
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,919
How quick?

61
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,239
Call this number.

62
00:04:35,239 --> 00:04:36,399
It gets you

63
00:04:36,399 --> 00:04:38,645
close to two grand a day.

64
00:04:38,645 --> 00:04:40,080
[Computer Geek Repair]
[Yang Gang]

65
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,520
I can't do this job.

66
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,640
Why not?

67
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:46,760
I know this guy.

68
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,719
He deals in stolen goods.

69
00:04:48,719 --> 00:04:50,880
I wouldn't take that kind of money.

70
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:53,080
Money is money.

71
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,359
Who cares where it comes from?

72
00:04:54,359 --> 00:04:57,000
There's a famous saying: "Clean money lets you

73
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,599
spend with peace of mine."

74
00:04:58,599 --> 00:05:00,080
Who said that?

75
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:02,279
The philosopher, Zhou Gui Mei.

76
00:05:02,279 --> 00:05:04,237
Who's that?

77
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,311
Not telling you.

78
00:05:07,951 --> 00:05:09,240
It is done.

79
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,646
So fast?

80
00:05:16,990 --> 00:05:19,335
Thank you, baby, for the big yacht!

81
00:05:19,335 --> 00:05:20,400
Thank you.

82
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:23,920
Thanks for the gift. Thanks! Awesome!!

83
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:26,039
Thank you.

84
00:05:26,039 --> 00:05:28,247
Who the hell are you?

85
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,511
Can you keep it down?

86
00:05:31,511 --> 00:05:34,599
- What did you say?
- I said, can you keep it down?

87
00:05:34,599 --> 00:05:36,516
Then come in here and adjust
the volume yourself! Come on.

88
00:05:36,516 --> 00:05:40,360
- Go ahead, adjust it. Let's see what you mean.
- let me go or I'll scream for help!

89
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,480
Let go of me!

90
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,653
Take it easy, man. Calm down.

91
00:05:43,653 --> 00:05:45,760
This is my cousin.
She's been spoiled rotten by her family.

92
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:47,000
She's a bit high-maintenance,

93
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,200
has a sharp tongue,

94
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,760
and a bad temper.

95
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:51,520
Please bear with her.

96
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,839
She's your cousin?

97
00:05:52,839 --> 00:05:54,279
- Yes.
- How did you raise her?

98
00:05:54,279 --> 00:05:56,399
She came to my place early in the morning,
shouting and yelling,

99
00:05:56,399 --> 00:05:58,039
telling me to keep it down.

100
00:05:58,039 --> 00:06:00,599
Sorry. My cousin has trouble sleeping.

101
00:06:00,599 --> 00:06:02,919
Whenever there's noise,
she usually yells at me.

102
00:06:02,919 --> 00:06:05,159
I wasn't around this morning,
so she came after you.

103
00:06:05,159 --> 00:06:07,479
I'm truly sorry.

104
00:06:07,479 --> 00:06:08,811
I'll let it slide today for your sake.

105
00:06:08,811 --> 00:06:10,877
Watch it next time.

106
00:06:14,399 --> 00:06:15,880
How am I high-maintenance?

107
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:17,000
You're not.

108
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,880
Just stop meddling in others' business.

109
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:21,479
How am I meddling?

110
00:06:21,479 --> 00:06:24,040
Do you know my grandma better than I do?

111
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:28,200
You mean about ordering the food?

112
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,359
The portions here are just so huge.

113
00:06:30,359 --> 00:06:33,652
I couldn't finish it all by myself,
so I shared it with Grandma.

114
00:06:35,039 --> 00:06:37,200
Why are you here anyway?

115
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,017
To fix the Wi-Fi.

116
00:06:39,719 --> 00:06:42,298
You're the one fixing the Wi-Fi?

117
00:06:43,919 --> 00:06:45,399
I heard you didn't have

118
00:06:45,399 --> 00:06:47,770
a very good night last night.

119
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:50,239
I'm doing great.

120
00:06:50,239 --> 00:06:52,640
At least there's air conditioning here.

121
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,934
It's much better than Xuan Island.

122
00:07:04,466 --> 00:07:06,370
Sorry to break it to you,

123
00:07:06,370 --> 00:07:07,839
but the air conditioning...

124
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:09,923
was also fixed by me.

125
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,880
Hello.

126
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,000
Are you extending your stay?

127
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,421
I am.

128
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,000
Wait, the payment didn't go through.

129
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,187
T-Try scanning it again.

130
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:42,839
Let me handle it.

131
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:44,920
Okay.

132
00:07:58,163 --> 00:08:01,279
Uncle Sun,
please reply as soon as you see this message.

133
00:08:01,279 --> 00:08:03,212
It's urgent.

134
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:14,560
Our spendthrift

135
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,411
has money to burn.

136
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,239
I sent you the room fee.

137
00:08:19,239 --> 00:08:21,478
You decide whether to extend.

138
00:08:28,147 --> 00:08:30,479
The AC is fixed.

139
00:08:30,479 --> 00:08:32,119
The guy next door is a long-term tenant.

140
00:08:32,119 --> 00:08:33,640
If you want to listen to his stream,

141
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,160
go ahead.

142
00:08:37,908 --> 00:08:40,239
Thanks for the gift, "Little Cutie"!
Thank you, "My Sky"!

143
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:45,024
So... extending?

144
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:46,900
I'm checking out.

145
00:09:08,759 --> 00:09:11,600
How did you get here?

146
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,205
Where is your home?

147
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,450
No home, just like me?

148
00:09:18,471 --> 00:09:19,479
Let me see.

149
00:09:19,479 --> 00:09:20,759
What's your name?

150
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:22,280
Oh, you have a tag!

151
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:24,759
Ta Ta, is it?

152
00:09:24,759 --> 00:09:27,267
Your name is Ta Ta?

153
00:09:29,719 --> 00:09:31,988
Where is your home?

154
00:09:32,819 --> 00:09:34,248
Ta Ta.

155
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:37,839
I told you not to run off.

156
00:09:37,839 --> 00:09:38,999
It's raining so hard.

157
00:09:38,999 --> 00:09:41,008
What if you got lost?

158
00:09:41,999 --> 00:09:44,239
Is this yours?

159
00:09:44,239 --> 00:09:47,107
Let's go. I'll take you home to your mom.

160
00:10:01,906 --> 00:10:02,920
Once you leave here,

161
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:05,119
Turn left and walk 500 meters,
and you'll find a bus stop.

162
00:10:05,119 --> 00:10:07,000
Three stops and you'll be back in Xuan Island.

163
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,935
So naggy.

164
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,879
[Bus 19: First bus 6:00, Last bus 21:30]
[Bus 51]

165
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:39,129
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

166
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,881
[Uncle Sun]

167
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:07,479
Hello?

168
00:11:07,479 --> 00:11:09,839
Ye, did you call me?

169
00:11:09,839 --> 00:11:11,359
I was busy just now.

170
00:11:11,359 --> 00:11:12,519
Uncle Sun,

171
00:11:12,519 --> 00:11:14,839
my bank card has been frozen.

172
00:11:14,839 --> 00:11:18,080
Is it because of my dad? What happened?

173
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,960
The case is quite complicated.

174
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:22,239
This is part of
the normal investigation procedure.

175
00:11:22,239 --> 00:11:24,101
Don't worry too much.

176
00:11:25,719 --> 00:11:27,479
I see.

177
00:11:27,479 --> 00:11:29,519
I've transferred some money to you.

178
00:11:29,519 --> 00:11:31,119
Tell me if it's not enough.

179
00:11:31,119 --> 00:11:32,999
Okay.

180
00:11:32,999 --> 00:11:36,198
Thanks for your help, Uncle Sun.

181
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:47,242
[Let me know if you need more.]

182
00:12:10,639 --> 00:12:12,479
Auntie.

183
00:12:12,479 --> 00:12:15,519
Why are you coming in from outside?

184
00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:16,640
I...

185
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,519
I-I went out for a walk.

186
00:12:18,519 --> 00:12:19,519
A walk?

187
00:12:19,519 --> 00:12:21,891
A walk with a suitcase?

188
00:12:23,599 --> 00:12:25,426
I just want to carry a heavy load.

189
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,774
Oh yeah!

190
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:31,115
Here. Take this.

191
00:12:32,719 --> 00:12:35,479
Just keep it.

192
00:12:35,479 --> 00:12:38,879
Wu said he can't let you pay for that lock.

193
00:12:38,879 --> 00:12:40,519
Besides, you've already paid

194
00:12:40,519 --> 00:12:41,920
for your room and board here.

195
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,599
We can't take another cent from you.

196
00:12:43,599 --> 00:12:45,960
Otherwise, he'll argue with me again.

197
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:48,320
Also,

198
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,879
red bean zongzi.

199
00:12:49,879 --> 00:12:51,224
Try some.

200
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,280
I'm not hungry. I won't eat.

201
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:57,000
No, this wasn't fried in lard.

202
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,120
Wu switched it to rapeseed oil.

203
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,920
Really, he fried it just for you.

204
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:03,752
Try it and see how it is.

205
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:07,051
Come on, try it.

206
00:13:20,479 --> 00:13:24,680
- It's actually quite good.
- Good, right? I told you.

207
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:26,545
I want to try some too.

208
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,040
Auntie,

209
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,280
I was a bit out of line yesterday.

210
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,960
Please don't take it to heart.

211
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,239
Let me tell you,

212
00:13:35,239 --> 00:13:39,879
lard and rapeseed oil
really taste different when fried.

213
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:43,215
What did you just say? W-What was that?

214
00:13:44,519 --> 00:13:46,024
Nothing.

215
00:13:46,024 --> 00:13:47,160
It's delicious.

216
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,800
Right? I think so too.

217
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,280
I'm going back to my room now.

218
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:51,719
Wait, wait, wait.

219
00:13:51,719 --> 00:13:53,680
Take another one.

220
00:13:53,680 --> 00:13:55,239
I'll pick a big piece for you.

221
00:13:55,239 --> 00:13:56,920
Okay.

222
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:58,320
Eat up, okay?

223
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:00,133
- I'm going upstairs then.
- Okay.

224
00:14:07,719 --> 00:14:09,680
Where's my laptop bag?

225
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:11,800
What laptop bag?

226
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:14,920
Oh no! I had two bags with me.
One black, one pink.

227
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:17,470
I never saw a pink one...

228
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,765
W-What's wrong?

229
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:23,613
Ye.

230
00:14:35,063 --> 00:14:37,200
Hello, Zhang,

231
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,719
it's me.

232
00:14:38,719 --> 00:14:40,864
Fang from Xuan Island.

233
00:14:40,864 --> 00:14:44,061
Your mom comes to my place often
to get her hair cut.

234
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,406
It's like this.

235
00:14:51,406 --> 00:14:54,879
My niece lost her laptop on the bus.

236
00:14:54,879 --> 00:14:58,545
Yes. I want to see if you can help find it.

237
00:15:00,974 --> 00:15:01,999
Right, right.

238
00:15:01,999 --> 00:15:05,280
Got it. When your mom comes by for a perm,

239
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,920
I'll give her a twenty percent discount.

240
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:08,151
Gotta go.

241
00:15:09,639 --> 00:15:11,354
The odds aren't great.

242
00:15:12,552 --> 00:15:14,320
Then I'll go file a report
at the police station.

243
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,440
I'll ask the police

244
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:17,549
to check the surveillance footage.

245
00:15:18,479 --> 00:15:20,680
Get ready for a needle in a haystack.

246
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,400
What do you mean?

247
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:25,400
That laptop of yours? In all of Zhazhating,
there are only a few like it.

248
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,960
If it's stolen, there are only two outcomes.

249
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:28,160
Either they keep it for themselves,

250
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:29,960
or they sell it for cash.

251
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,960
That computer of mine
has a lot of important stuff on it.

252
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:35,599
I have to get it back.

253
00:15:35,599 --> 00:15:37,800
Wu, you know a lot of people

254
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:38,876
and have many connections.

255
00:15:38,876 --> 00:15:41,040
Why don't you help her look for it?

256
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,868
It might be more effective than
the CCTV footage.

257
00:15:48,479 --> 00:15:50,359
If you don't want to help, forget it.

258
00:15:50,359 --> 00:15:52,279
I'll go to the police.

259
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:55,800
Then I'll go with you.

260
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,280
You're a stranger in a strange land.

261
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:59,082
Ye.

262
00:16:01,679 --> 00:16:03,399
Call this number.

263
00:16:04,399 --> 00:16:05,519
Guarantees you

264
00:16:05,519 --> 00:16:07,159
close to two grand a day.

265
00:16:12,399 --> 00:16:13,899
Hello?

266
00:16:17,407 --> 00:16:18,519
Okay, okay.

267
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,556
Alright, thanks for your hard work.

268
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:25,080
Officer Xu, how is it going?

269
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,639
Let's sit down and talk. Come on.

270
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:28,440
Has the security in Zhazhating

271
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,559
become this bad?

272
00:16:29,559 --> 00:16:31,399
She just stepped out and her computer
was stolen.

273
00:16:31,399 --> 00:16:33,679
I really want to see who this thief
actually is.

274
00:16:33,679 --> 00:16:36,159
What's the rush? Can't we sit down and talk?

275
00:16:36,159 --> 00:16:38,080
That laptop is really expensive.

276
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,399
I can't sit still.

277
00:16:39,399 --> 00:16:41,599
We've already looked into your situation.

278
00:16:41,599 --> 00:16:43,800
Just now, I called the bus company.

279
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:47,479
I asked them to send over the footage
from the relevant time period.

280
00:16:47,479 --> 00:16:49,160
The volume of footage is quite large.

281
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:51,549
It'll take some time to transfer.

282
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:53,900
Well...

283
00:16:54,479 --> 00:16:55,839
How about this?

284
00:16:55,839 --> 00:16:57,359
Auntie, you go back to the shop.

285
00:16:57,359 --> 00:16:59,519
I'll watch it myself.

286
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:01,960
That's great.

287
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,680
- Thank you, Officer Xu.
- You're welcome.

288
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:05,378
I'm leaving.

289
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,079
Then come with me.

290
00:17:23,239 --> 00:17:24,319
I'm here.

291
00:17:24,319 --> 00:17:26,039
Where are you?

292
00:17:26,039 --> 00:17:27,479
Keep going straight.

293
00:17:27,479 --> 00:17:28,479
There's a blue door.

294
00:17:28,479 --> 00:17:31,277
Honk twice when you get there.

295
00:17:46,479 --> 00:17:48,614
You must be Xing Wu.

296
00:17:49,479 --> 00:17:50,999
That's me.

297
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:58,079
I've heard a lot about you.

298
00:17:58,079 --> 00:18:00,400
I heard you have a history with Cao Ping.

299
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:17,239
Does that have anything to do
with taking the job?

300
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:21,600
Fair point.

301
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,799
The grudge between you two has
noting to do with me.

302
00:18:22,799 --> 00:18:25,221
He'll settle it with you when he gets out.

303
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:27,400
Come on in.

304
00:18:52,239 --> 00:18:54,666
Yes, that's him.

305
00:18:58,079 --> 00:19:00,872
He's blocking his face, it's hard to see.

306
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:03,640
Looks like a repeat offender.

307
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:05,600
He didn't show his face at all.

308
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,759
Can I get my laptop back?

309
00:19:08,759 --> 00:19:10,079
We'll do our best.

310
00:19:10,079 --> 00:19:12,808
Okay, thank you then.

311
00:19:18,719 --> 00:19:20,039
So, what do you think?

312
00:19:20,039 --> 00:19:21,680
This place is pretty good.

313
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:23,479
Is my business

314
00:19:23,479 --> 00:19:25,319
big enough for you?

315
00:19:25,319 --> 00:19:27,120
Do you like it?

316
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:39,160
Can you handle this much work?

317
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,479
I can't.

318
00:19:40,479 --> 00:19:42,840
That's why I'm short-staffed.

319
00:19:48,779 --> 00:19:50,239
Buddy,

320
00:19:50,239 --> 00:19:53,735
how long does it usually take you
to change a phone battery?

321
00:19:54,479 --> 00:19:55,559
About five minutes.

322
00:19:55,559 --> 00:19:56,640
Five minutes?

323
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,140
You...

324
00:20:03,079 --> 00:20:05,079
Show me you can do it in five minutes.

325
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:52,880
Not bad, bro!

326
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,079
You're faster than both

327
00:20:54,079 --> 00:20:56,519
my technicians combined.

328
00:20:56,519 --> 00:20:57,880
I heard you have...

329
00:20:57,880 --> 00:21:00,079
tougher jobs here.

330
00:21:00,079 --> 00:21:02,073
And better pay?

331
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,719
Want to make money?

332
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:07,920
- Yes.
- Straightforward.

333
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,680
Then show me what you can do.

334
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:10,960
Come.

335
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:13,559
Come here.

336
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:20,519
Newer devices

337
00:21:20,519 --> 00:21:21,960
get flashed and refurbished.

338
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:24,920
Worn-out ones are stripped for parts.

339
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,880
You get paid per piece.

340
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:33,479
You are pretty sharp.

341
00:21:33,479 --> 00:21:35,479
I just got it.

342
00:21:35,479 --> 00:21:36,519
Wipe the accounts,

343
00:21:36,519 --> 00:21:38,680
flash it, then sell it as new.

344
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:43,261
Sourced through a legal channel?

345
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:46,120
Don't ask what you should not ask.

346
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:48,519
You'll get paid.

347
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:53,120
Gang,

348
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:54,840
I am not cut out

349
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:58,079
for anything illegal.

350
00:21:58,079 --> 00:21:59,485
How about this,

351
00:21:59,485 --> 00:22:02,461
I am here to buy something today.

352
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:04,960
What do you mean?

353
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:06,492
I will take this one.

354
00:22:06,492 --> 00:22:08,299
Name your price.

355
00:22:11,999 --> 00:22:13,239
Fine.

356
00:22:14,239 --> 00:22:15,920
16,000 yuan.

357
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:20,160
If you can pay the price,
the laptop is yours.

358
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,840
You bought this for less than 2,000 yuan.

359
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:25,079
Now you are selling it to me at full price.

360
00:22:25,079 --> 00:22:26,519
Do you take me for a fool?

361
00:22:26,519 --> 00:22:27,905
Xing Wu,

362
00:22:28,612 --> 00:22:30,880
are you here to cause trouble?

363
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:34,680
Listen,

364
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:35,880
if you can't pay,

365
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:39,296
neither you nor the laptop is leaving.

366
00:22:41,479 --> 00:22:43,680
What if I insist on leaving?

367
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:46,920
Then it depends

368
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,400
on whether you have what it takes.

369
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:56,200
You have so many phones
and laptops of unknown origin.

370
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,355
Do you want to go back to prison again?

371
00:23:00,056 --> 00:23:01,281
You know

372
00:23:01,281 --> 00:23:03,501
how Cao Ping ended up in prison.

373
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,660
Hello?

374
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:18,162
Wu, take it easy.

375
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:19,920
Can I take the laptop?

376
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,745
Take it. Take it.

377
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:26,039
2,000 yuan.

378
00:23:26,039 --> 00:23:28,279
Money can be earned back.

379
00:23:28,279 --> 00:23:30,079
You know the rules.

380
00:23:31,319 --> 00:23:32,719
Yeah.

381
00:23:32,719 --> 00:23:34,259
I know.

382
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:36,759
Wu, take the money and we're done.

383
00:23:36,759 --> 00:23:38,360
Goodbye.

384
00:23:59,559 --> 00:24:00,759
Officer Xu.

385
00:24:00,759 --> 00:24:02,880
I found something wrong
with Yang Gang's repair center.

386
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:05,039
You should keep an eye on it.

387
00:24:13,279 --> 00:24:15,519
Auntie, I'm back.

388
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:18,160
You're back.

389
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:19,239
I fell asleep.

390
00:24:19,239 --> 00:24:21,239
How was it? Have you found the thief?

391
00:24:21,239 --> 00:24:22,600
I found him,

392
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:24,039
but I didn't see his face clearly.

393
00:24:24,039 --> 00:24:25,479
Did not see his face?

394
00:24:25,479 --> 00:24:27,840
Then... what about the laptop?

395
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:30,360
The laptop... Officer Xu said

396
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:31,479
it is still under investigation.

397
00:24:31,479 --> 00:24:33,600
It'll take some time.

398
00:24:35,759 --> 00:24:38,559
Alright. Don't worry about it.

399
00:24:38,559 --> 00:24:41,479
It is still under investigation anyway.

400
00:24:42,519 --> 00:24:44,682
My laptop?

401
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,640
I knew it.

402
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:51,039
Zhazhating

403
00:24:51,039 --> 00:24:53,880
is full of talented people
and beautiful scenery.

404
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:54,999
There are kind people

405
00:24:54,999 --> 00:24:56,360
who quietly do good deeds here.

406
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:57,680
Check it. Is it in good condition?

407
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,563
It is fine.

408
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:04,680
I guess my luck is just too good.

409
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:07,999
So once people knew we lost a laptop,

410
00:25:07,999 --> 00:25:10,200
they returned it.

411
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,519
If it were me,

412
00:25:11,519 --> 00:25:13,680
I'd definitely give this kind person

413
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,360
a banner of thanks.

414
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:20,031
And I would even kowtow three times

415
00:25:20,731 --> 00:25:25,799
to show my sincere gratitude.

416
00:25:26,627 --> 00:25:28,547
You found the laptop?

417
00:25:30,519 --> 00:25:33,279
Son, you're home?

418
00:25:33,279 --> 00:25:35,693
It's found!

419
00:25:36,719 --> 00:25:37,960
Since the laptop is back,

420
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:39,559
I'll head next door.

421
00:25:39,559 --> 00:25:41,160
Remember to feed Fa Cai.

422
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,400
Don't keep feeding Yao Ji.

423
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,200
It is getting fat. I'm off now.

424
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:46,892
The skinny one is Yao Ji.

425
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:00,799
Can you even tell which is Fa Cai

426
00:26:00,799 --> 00:26:02,653
and which is Yao Ji?

427
00:26:03,519 --> 00:26:05,757
Of course I can.

428
00:26:09,999 --> 00:26:11,400
This one,

429
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:12,680
the thinnest and smallest,

430
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:14,200
is Yao Ji.

431
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:15,840
This one is Bai Ban.

432
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:17,640
That one is Fa Cai.

433
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:25,999
You're hurt.

434
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:30,680
It's nothing.

435
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:34,912
My laptop...

436
00:26:35,559 --> 00:26:37,883
You were the one who
found my laptop, right?

437
00:26:43,759 --> 00:26:45,479
If you want to think so,

438
00:26:45,479 --> 00:26:47,364
it could be me.

439
00:26:50,920 --> 00:26:52,519
What?

440
00:26:52,519 --> 00:26:55,015
Want to kowtow to me three times?

441
00:26:55,015 --> 00:26:56,774
In your dreams.

442
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:10,680
He doesn't seem

443
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:13,319
as terrible as I thought.

444
00:27:32,279 --> 00:27:33,920
What's up?

445
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:44,400
I have some medicine left

446
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:45,920
from Dr. Zhuang.

447
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,420
Take it.

448
00:27:53,005 --> 00:27:55,412
It is just a minor injury.
I do not need it.

449
00:28:09,239 --> 00:28:10,840
Thanks anyway.

450
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:14,680
They beat you up like this.

451
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:16,680
Did you call the police?

452
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:18,519
I told Officer Xu.

453
00:28:18,519 --> 00:28:20,437
They'll investigate.

454
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,587
Xing Wu?

455
00:29:07,479 --> 00:29:09,479
What are you doing here?

456
00:29:11,218 --> 00:29:12,709
Working?

457
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:16,479
I suggest you do not stand here.

458
00:29:16,479 --> 00:29:17,479
Why?

459
00:29:17,479 --> 00:29:19,403
Am I in your way?

460
00:29:21,519 --> 00:29:23,501
I'm afraid you'll get hit.

461
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:26,479
You're scaring me again.

462
00:29:28,559 --> 00:29:29,799
Believe it or not.

463
00:29:29,799 --> 00:29:31,079
I don't believe you.

464
00:29:31,079 --> 00:29:33,759
Make way. Move...

465
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,920
It's my turn.

466
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,680
Give me a good hand.

467
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:54,999
4-bamboo tile.

468
00:29:54,999 --> 00:29:56,396
- My turn.
- Right, I forgot.

469
00:29:56,396 --> 00:29:59,424
What are you thinking about?

470
00:29:59,424 --> 00:30:00,544
West Wind.

471
00:30:00,544 --> 00:30:02,436
West Wind.

472
00:30:02,436 --> 00:30:06,360
- Did I get it wrong? It's my turn.
- 1-bamboo tile.

473
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:07,508
Auntie.

474
00:30:07,508 --> 00:30:10,880
The Wi-Fi... keeps cutting out.
Is something wrong with it?

475
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:14,146
The Wi-Fi on the second floor is bad.
There is a router next to the cashier.

476
00:30:14,146 --> 00:30:16,880
Just unplug it and plug it back in.

477
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:19,091
West Wind.

478
00:30:34,566 --> 00:30:37,719
Cousin. Here's the fruit you wanted.

479
00:30:37,719 --> 00:30:39,039
I went to the town to buy them.

480
00:30:39,039 --> 00:30:41,200
It is special, just for you.

481
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:44,276
- ♫I just want to show you my care♫
- Stop, stop.

482
00:30:44,276 --> 00:30:48,307
I asked for imported cherries and avocados.

483
00:30:49,519 --> 00:30:50,960
Don't you think I know that?

484
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:53,160
Imported cherries are just cherries.

485
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:55,517
As for the avocados...

486
00:30:55,517 --> 00:30:57,279
I went to two stores
and still could not find it.

487
00:30:57,279 --> 00:30:58,960
Just eat. Try the figs.

488
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:01,920
Same thing. They're all fruit.

489
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:02,960
You... you...

490
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,799
Are they washed?

491
00:31:04,799 --> 00:31:06,550
Are they washed?

492
00:31:06,550 --> 00:31:08,640
Yeah, they're washed.

493
00:31:13,006 --> 00:31:14,782
How is it?

494
00:31:14,782 --> 00:31:17,680
The fruit in Zhazhating isn't bad, right?

495
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,479
Not bad.

496
00:31:19,479 --> 00:31:22,200
If you like them, I'll buy them
for you every day.

497
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:24,680
- Fuzz!
- Eat.

498
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,960
Come and help out.

499
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:28,120
- Okay.
- Hao Cheng Gong.

500
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:30,239
Eat up, Cousin.

501
00:31:30,239 --> 00:31:33,002
Nag, nag, nag.

502
00:31:33,961 --> 00:31:35,793
1-dot tile.

503
00:31:36,999 --> 00:31:39,279
Give me a good hand!

504
00:31:39,279 --> 00:31:40,759
What's this?

505
00:31:40,759 --> 00:31:43,360
- 4-bamboo tile.
- Give me a good hand.

506
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:46,240
Ye, my... my mom

507
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:48,664
made it especially for you.

508
00:31:49,276 --> 00:31:51,031
That's so much.

509
00:31:51,031 --> 00:31:52,039
She said,

510
00:31:52,039 --> 00:31:53,680
you should have four dishes
and a soup per meal too.

511
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:55,279
But the portions are halved.

512
00:31:55,279 --> 00:31:56,559
This is halved?

513
00:31:56,559 --> 00:31:58,417
This... This is just a
standard portion in Zhazhating.

514
00:31:58,417 --> 00:32:01,039
Help yourself.

515
00:32:01,039 --> 00:32:02,279
Eat some fruit.

516
00:32:02,279 --> 00:32:03,840
Hello, bosses.

517
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:05,360
Time to eat!

518
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:06,719
You've worked hard, son.

519
00:32:06,719 --> 00:32:07,999
Hurry up, I'm starving.

520
00:32:07,999 --> 00:32:09,719
- I'm hungry too.
- Hurry, hurry.

521
00:32:09,719 --> 00:32:12,600
- Coming right up!
- Don't put it there.

522
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,319
Thank you, son.

523
00:32:14,319 --> 00:32:15,799
Your mom is one tile away from winning.

524
00:32:15,799 --> 00:32:17,120
Try one.

525
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,474
Have one.

526
00:32:21,719 --> 00:32:23,200
You little cutie Hu.

527
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,999
You look so innocent and honest,

528
00:32:24,999 --> 00:32:26,479
but you're playing favorites!

529
00:32:26,479 --> 00:32:29,120
Look! The fish balls in your mom's bowl

530
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,200
are more than all of ours combined!

531
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:35,519
It wasn't me. My dad just hand-rolled
these fish balls.

532
00:32:35,519 --> 00:32:37,200
He wanted my mom to have more.

533
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:39,880
I see. It's not playing favorites.

534
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:44,400
It's your dad's...
exclusive affection for your mom.

535
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:45,799
Hurry up and eat yours.

536
00:32:45,799 --> 00:32:46,999
Go take some to Grandma.

537
00:32:46,999 --> 00:32:48,200
Grandma, time to eat.

538
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,559
- Whose turn is it? Whose turn?
- Whose turn?

539
00:32:49,559 --> 00:32:51,880
- My turn, my turn, my turn!
- Hurry up.

540
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:54,039
- Give me a good one. Seven Circles!
- Don't interrupt.

541
00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:56,120
What are you thinking for?
Just play it and be done with it.

542
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:58,840
- What are you doing?
- Go on, go do what you need to do.

543
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,400
Son, you are off? Don't forget to
take your medicine.

544
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,672
Mom, remember to have the meal.

545
00:33:02,672 --> 00:33:03,880
Hu,

546
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:05,559
Does Zhazhating

547
00:33:05,559 --> 00:33:08,759
have any other specialties?

548
00:33:08,759 --> 00:33:11,722
- Of course.
- There definitely are.

549
00:33:17,479 --> 00:33:20,640
What are all these?

550
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:23,360
This is our local specialty drink.

551
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:24,759
Zhazha Drink.

552
00:33:24,759 --> 00:33:27,031
It's delicious.

553
00:33:32,079 --> 00:33:34,120
- It's not bad.
- Here.

554
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:35,759
Try some specialty skewers in Zhazhating.

555
00:33:35,759 --> 00:33:37,912
Zhazha Skewers.

556
00:33:43,079 --> 00:33:44,719
- How is it?
- This is good too.

557
00:33:44,719 --> 00:33:46,200
Right?

558
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:48,165
It's okay.

559
00:33:49,173 --> 00:33:50,519
By the way,

560
00:33:50,519 --> 00:33:52,120
why did Wu drop out of school?

561
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:53,799
He dropped out a long time ago.

562
00:33:53,799 --> 00:33:55,400
He's been out in the world for two years.

563
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:56,400
He...

564
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,999
He quit during his senior year.

565
00:33:58,999 --> 00:34:02,600
His mom has been keeping his enrollment active.

566
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:04,360
Wu has to earn money.

567
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:05,600
A family of three...

568
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:07,120
plus Liu Nian.

569
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:09,303
They all depend on him.

570
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,639
Anyway, he's just one word:

571
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:13,244
Awesome.

572
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:15,479
That impressive?

573
00:34:15,479 --> 00:34:16,720
He's smart and tough.

574
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:18,479
He can fix anything.

575
00:34:18,479 --> 00:34:19,999
And he's the most loyal.

576
00:34:19,999 --> 00:34:21,800
A good brother.

577
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:23,320
The head of the family.

578
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:25,639
He's very responsible.

579
00:34:25,639 --> 00:34:26,679
To put it simply,

580
00:34:26,679 --> 00:34:28,479
he's the most promising

581
00:34:28,479 --> 00:34:30,400
and amazing man in Zhazhating.

582
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:34,039
He's a Zhazhating specialty too.

583
00:34:34,039 --> 00:34:35,920
He's not "scam" - he's great.

584
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:37,240
How great can he be?

585
00:34:37,240 --> 00:34:39,039
Can he fly to the moon?

586
00:34:39,039 --> 00:34:41,079
Actually, he almost did.

587
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:43,519
The plane he made flew so high.

588
00:34:43,519 --> 00:34:45,159
Wu used to be a top student.

589
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:48,039
Shortly after his senior year started,
he dropped out.

590
00:34:48,039 --> 00:34:49,240
He had no choice.

591
00:34:49,240 --> 00:34:50,880
Our teacher and Aunt Lanfang

592
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:52,280
both wanted him to return.

593
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,280
If it weren't for two years ago...

594
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:54,599
Fuzz,

595
00:34:54,599 --> 00:34:56,360
Watch your mouth.

596
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:59,559
Didn't Wu forbid you
from talking about his past?

597
00:34:59,559 --> 00:35:02,400
She isn't an outsider.

598
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:04,862
If it weren't for two years ago...

599
00:35:07,479 --> 00:35:09,999
If you're curious, ask him yourself.

600
00:35:09,999 --> 00:35:12,280
I'm not that curious.

601
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:14,240
Wh-Whose computer is this?

602
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:15,730
Pocky, what are you doing?

603
00:35:15,730 --> 00:35:17,639
Why did you splash water on it?

604
00:35:17,639 --> 00:35:18,639
- It's fine.
- Oh! Hurry, hurry!

605
00:35:18,639 --> 00:35:20,440
It's just a little water.

606
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:23,157
What's wrong?

607
00:35:23,157 --> 00:35:24,559
Oh! My computer...

608
00:35:24,559 --> 00:35:27,360
I haven't picked my classes yet. It...

609
00:35:30,479 --> 00:35:31,880
It won't turn on.

610
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:34,008
- It's soaked.
- It's okay, just a little water.

611
00:35:34,008 --> 00:35:35,100
I'll wipe it with a rag.

612
00:35:35,100 --> 00:35:36,601
A hair dryer will fix it right up.

613
00:35:36,601 --> 00:35:39,720
- No, no, no!
- She needs that computer to go abroad.

614
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:42,360
I was just having a cup of water.
I didn't see her computer right there.

615
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,599
Is it that serious?

616
00:35:43,599 --> 00:35:45,280
I'll pay for the damages.

617
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:48,159
This computer has high-end specs.

618
00:35:48,159 --> 00:35:50,999
It'll cost at least a thousand to fix.

619
00:35:51,999 --> 00:35:53,920
That expensive?

620
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:55,240
You've really done it now.

621
00:35:55,240 --> 00:35:57,559
Why not let Wu take a look?

622
00:35:57,559 --> 00:35:59,103
Right, Wu can fix it.

623
00:35:59,103 --> 00:36:01,283
Do you have an authorized service center?

624
00:36:01,283 --> 00:36:02,270
Service center? No.

625
00:36:02,270 --> 00:36:04,639
- I don't think so.
- No, never heard of one.

626
00:36:04,639 --> 00:36:06,400
Then, where is the nearest repair shop?

627
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:07,639
Where is it?

628
00:36:07,639 --> 00:36:09,479
- It's at Erqiao.
- Erqiao.

629
00:36:09,479 --> 00:36:11,880
Qing Ye! Qing...

630
00:36:20,559 --> 00:36:23,159
Sir! Can you ride me to Erqiao?

631
00:36:23,159 --> 00:36:25,039
Little girl, it's you again.

632
00:36:25,039 --> 00:36:26,570
Let's go! Come on.

633
00:36:26,570 --> 00:36:30,755
By the way, please take me to
the best computer repairman around here.

634
00:36:30,755 --> 00:36:32,479
Then you've hailed the right car.

635
00:36:32,479 --> 00:36:34,892
Sit tight and put on the helmet.

636
00:36:44,999 --> 00:36:48,339
♪ Let me accept ♪

637
00:36:53,720 --> 00:36:54,880
Sir.

638
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:56,760
Sir, could you please go faster?

639
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,240
Little girl,

640
00:36:58,240 --> 00:36:59,400
in our life,

641
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:01,400
we shouldn't always be in such a rush.

642
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:03,840
We should stop once in a while

643
00:37:03,840 --> 00:37:05,599
to enjoy the scenery along the way.

644
00:37:05,599 --> 00:37:07,119
Don't you think so?

645
00:37:08,119 --> 00:37:10,360
I'll pay double.

646
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:11,840
It's not about the money.

647
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:14,320
I'm not even charging you for this.

648
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:16,280
But I'm in a hurry, sir.

649
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:18,064
It's an absolute emergency.

650
00:37:18,064 --> 00:37:19,304
An absolute emergency?

651
00:37:19,304 --> 00:37:20,720
Why didn't you say so earlier?

652
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:22,320
Hold on tight.

653
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:23,920
Here we go!

654
00:37:38,091 --> 00:37:39,639
We're here, little girl.

655
00:37:39,639 --> 00:37:42,320
For phone and computer repairs,
Ju Huang is the place.

656
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:44,320
Ju Huang?

657
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:45,530
Trust me, you can't go wrong.

658
00:37:45,530 --> 00:37:47,199
Go on.

659
00:37:47,199 --> 00:37:49,260
- Thanks.
- Sure thing.

660
00:37:57,679 --> 00:37:59,199
Hello.

661
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:12,280
Hello.

662
00:38:14,392 --> 00:38:15,999
Who are you looking for?

663
00:38:15,999 --> 00:38:17,960
Are you Mr.Ju?

664
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:19,953
I'm here to get my computer fixed.

665
00:38:19,953 --> 00:38:21,780
Looking for Mr.Ju?

666
00:38:21,780 --> 00:38:22,960
Mr.Ju!

667
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:24,559
Someone's here for you.

668
00:38:24,559 --> 00:38:27,119
Come in. Look at this.

669
00:38:36,214 --> 00:38:38,285
You're Mr.Ju?

670
00:38:42,119 --> 00:38:43,320
Can I help you?

671
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:45,400
You know each other?

672
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:47,880
Then Wu, I'll come back for it when it's fixed.

673
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:48,999
I'll head out first.

674
00:38:48,999 --> 00:38:50,499
Okay.

675
00:38:53,720 --> 00:38:55,599
What's the problem?

676
00:38:55,599 --> 00:38:57,720
My laptop got wet. The screen is black.

677
00:38:57,720 --> 00:39:00,280
The tricycle driver said you could fix it.

678
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:08,800
Stolen yesterday, in for repair today.

679
00:39:08,800 --> 00:39:10,960
This laptop is quite unlucky with you.

680
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:13,400
I haven't had a single lucky day
since I got here.

681
00:39:37,720 --> 00:39:39,110
Why did you open it all up?

682
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:42,015
Do you know how to fix it? Don't break it.

683
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:52,639
Don't worry.

684
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:58,199
Wipe your sweat.

685
00:39:59,679 --> 00:40:01,479
Don't let it drip on my desk.

686
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:52,679
Don't worry. Have some water.

687
00:40:53,679 --> 00:40:55,639
Leave everything to Mr.Ju.

688
00:40:57,097 --> 00:40:58,240
I'm Canine.

689
00:40:58,240 --> 00:40:59,308
Wu's brother,

690
00:40:59,308 --> 00:41:00,720
and also half-owner here.

691
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:02,960
I'm Qing Ye.

692
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,690
Thank you.

693
00:41:04,690 --> 00:41:07,360
You can trust Wu's technical skills.

694
00:41:17,343 --> 00:41:19,079
How is it?

695
00:41:19,079 --> 00:41:20,999
A component on the motherboard is fried.

696
00:41:20,999 --> 00:41:22,519
It needs to be replaced.

697
00:41:22,519 --> 00:41:24,039
Can it be fixed by 10:00 p.m. tonight?

698
00:41:24,039 --> 00:41:25,199
I need it urgently.

699
00:41:25,199 --> 00:41:26,479
It's possible,

700
00:41:26,479 --> 00:41:28,084
but it'll be expensive.

701
00:41:28,084 --> 00:41:29,337
Money is no object.

702
00:41:29,337 --> 00:41:30,639
As long as you can fix it.

703
00:41:30,639 --> 00:41:32,760
Will the data inside be safe?

704
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,583
I can't guarantee that.

705
00:41:38,332 --> 00:41:39,760
What?

706
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:41,014
Got money again?

707
00:41:41,014 --> 00:41:42,133
Never mind that.

708
00:41:42,133 --> 00:41:44,972
I'll transfer the room fee to you as well.

709
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:51,800
What are you doing?

710
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:54,479
Are you going to fix my laptop, or what?

711
00:41:54,479 --> 00:41:56,880
The replacement part is in Xuan Island.

712
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:59,479
If you're coming, keep up.

713
00:42:05,790 --> 00:42:07,961
He's out! He's out!

714
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:19,937
Put this on.

715
00:42:19,937 --> 00:42:22,079
How am I supposed to sit on this?

716
00:42:24,479 --> 00:42:25,760
What are you looking at?

717
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:27,679
My apologies.

718
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:32,039
Get on.

719
00:42:32,039 --> 00:42:33,539
I...

720
00:43:03,199 --> 00:43:04,999
Fasten it yourself.

721
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:32,443
Need some help?

722
00:43:32,443 --> 00:43:34,360
No, I'm good.
